claim.claim-text:
1. Method of testing the functionality of a memory which operates at a high operating clock frequency, the method having the following steps: 
(a) generation of test data; 
(b) copying of the generated test data at the high operating clock frequency; 
(c) comparison of the copied test data with the generated test data; 
(d) generation of a functionality-indicating signal for indicating the functionality of the memory if the copied test data are identical to the generated test data.

10. Integrated synchronous memory with a multiplicity of addressable memory cells, which can be connected to an external circuit, with: 
a first self-testing circuit, for testing the functionality of the addressable memory cells; 
a second self-testing circuit, for testing the functionality of the high-frequency data exchange of the synchronous memory with the external circuit.
